<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">General distribution: Southern Europe</emphasis>
: Bulgaria, France, Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Gogala, Matija" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Slovenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="45 - 58" refId="B5742905" refString="Gogala, Matija, Trilar, Tomi, 2014. Distribution of endemic cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) on Evia and adjacent islands in Greece. Acta Entomologica Slovenica 22 (1): 45 - 58" title="Distribution of endemic cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) on Evia and adjacent islands in Greece" volume="22" year="2014">Gogala and Trilar 2014</bibRefCitation>
), Italy (
<bibRefCitation author="Hertach, Thomas" journalOrPublisher="Revue suisse de Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="229 - 269" refId="B6075365" refString="Hertach, Thomas, Nagel, Peter, 2013. Cicadas in Switzerland: a scientific overview of the historic and current knowledge of a popular taxon (Hemiptera: Cicadidae). Revue suisse de Zoologie 120 (2): 229 - 269" title="Cicadas in Switzerland: a scientific overview of the historic and current knowledge of a popular taxon (Hemiptera: Cicadidae)" volume="120" year="2013">Hertach and Nagel 2013</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Central Europe</emphasis>
: Switzerland; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Eastern Europe</emphasis>
: Russia (South European Russia), Ukraine; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Middle East</emphasis>
: Turkey; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Transcaucasia</emphasis>
: Armenia, Azerbaijan, Georgia (all data except for the countries with the citation in brackets are summarised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels, J P" journalOrPublisher="Dr W Junk Publisher, Dordrecht, Boston, Lancaster" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5742783" refString="Duffels, J P, van der Laan, P A, 1985. Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956-1980. Dr W Junk Publisher, Dordrecht, Boston, Lancaster" title="Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980" year="1985">Duffels and van der Laan 1985</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, Allen F" journalOrPublisher="Academic Press / Elsevier, London, UK" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5743532" refString="Sanborn, Allen F, 2014. Catalogue of the Cicadoidea. Academic Press/Elsevier, London, UK" title="Catalogue of the Cicadoidea" year="2014">Sanborn 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Distribution in Bulgaria</emphasis>
: This species is reported for Bulgaria as literature data, but without the citation of the source, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jankovic, Ljubodrag" journalOrPublisher="Acta Musei Macedonici Scientarium Naturalium" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="41 - 59" refId="B5743120" refString="Jankovic, Ljubodrag, 1971. Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha Makedonije. Acta Musei Macedonici Scientarium Naturalium 12 (3): 41 - 59" title="Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha Makedonije" volume="12" year="1971">
<normalizedToken originalValue="JankoviÄ‡">Jankovic</normalizedToken>
(1971)
</bibRefCitation>
for Petrich, which was erroneously placed in North Macedonia (
<bibRefCitation author="Gogala, Matija" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Slovenica" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="103 - 126" refId="B5742975" refString="Gogala, Matija, Trilar, Tomi, Krpac, Vladimir T, 2005. Fauna of singing cicadas (Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadoidea) of Macedonia - a bioacoustic survey. Acta Entomologica Slovenica 13 (2): 103 - 126" title="Fauna of singing cicadas (Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadoidea) of Macedonia - a bioacoustic survey" volume="13" year="2005">Gogala et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Petrich is a town in the Strumeshnitsa valley in SW Bulgaria, not far from the North Macedonian border. We recorded the singing males of this species on 23 July 2008 near Bozhkinoto on the slope of Belasitsa Mt. and confirmed their presence in this area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
In Bulgaria, data are known for 32 localities (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 73" captionStartId="F5781686" captionText="Figure 73. Map with localities of Tibicina steveni in Bulgaria. Black - literature data, blue - data from collections, red - bioacoustic data collected in this survey." figureDoi=".figure73" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/407208" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">73</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Krynicki" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tibicina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tibicina steveni" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steveni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Tibicina steveni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the southern part of the country along the Greek and Turkish borders. The data are known from Belasitsa Mt., Tundzha-Burgas Valley, eastern Rhodope Mts., Haskovo Hills Land, Sakar Mt. and Strandzha Mt. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 73" captionStartId="F5781686" captionText="Figure 73. Map with localities of Tibicina steveni in Bulgaria. Black - literature data, blue - data from collections, red - bioacoustic data collected in this survey." figureDoi=".figure73" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/407208" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">73</figureCitation>
) with altitude distribution between 20 and 820 m a.s.l. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 74" captionStartId="F5781690" captionText="Figure 74. Altitudinal distribution of Tibicina steveni. The percentage of the recorded localities is displayed in 200 - metre altitude zones." figureDoi=".figure74" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/407209" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">74</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">Acoustic behaviour</emphasis>
: The song was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Popov, Andrej V" journalOrPublisher="Entomologicheskoe obozrenie" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="258 - 290" refId="B5743411" refString="Popov, Andrej V, 1975. Stroenie timbalov i kharakteristika zvukovykh cignalov pevchikh tsikad (Homoptera, Cicadidae) yuzhnykh raionov SSSR [The structure of tymbals and characteristics of sound signals of singing cicadas (Homoptera, Cicadidae) from the southern regions of the USSR.- Entomological Review 54 (2): 7-36]. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie 54 (2): 258 - 290" title="Stroenie timbalov i kharakteristika zvukovykh cignalov pevchikh tsikad (Homoptera, Cicadidae) yuzhnykh raionov SSSR [The structure of tymbals and characteristics of sound signals of singing cicadas (Homoptera, Cicadidae) from the southern regions of the USSR. - Entomological Review 54 (2): 7 - 36]" volume="54" year="1975">Popov (1975)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sueur, Jerome" journalOrPublisher="Revue Francaise d'Entomologie (Nouvelle Serie)" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="105 - 111" refId="B5743732" refString="Sueur, Jerome, Puissant, Stephane, Pillet, J - M M, 2003. An eastern Mediterranean cicada in the west: first record of Tibicina steveni (Krynicki, 1837) in Switzerland and France [Hemiptera, Cicadidae, Tibicininae]. Revue Francaise d'Entomologie (Nouvelle Serie) 25 (3): 105 - 111" title="An eastern Mediterranean cicada in the west: first record of Tibicina steveni (Krynicki, 1837) in Switzerland and France [Hemiptera, Cicadidae, Tibicininae]" volume="25" year="2003">Sueur et al. (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sueur, Jerome" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="481 - 492" refId="B5743682" refString="Sueur, Jerome, Aubin, Thierry, 2003. Specificity of cicada calling songs in the genus Tibicina (Hemiptera: Cicadidae). Systematic Entomology 28 (4): 481 - 492" title="Specificity of cicada calling songs in the genus Tibicina (Hemiptera: Cicadidae)" volume="28" year="2003">Sueur and Aubin (2003)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">
The calling song (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 75" captionStartId="F5781694" captionText="Figure 75. Calling song of Tibicina steveni. (A) spectrogram and oscillogram of the selected part of the calling song; (B) oscillogram of the enlarged part corresponding to the inverted window in (A); (C) detailed oscillogram showing subgroups of pulses corresponding to the inverted window in (B); (D) detailed oscillogram showing pulses corresponding to the inverted window in (C)." figureDoi=".figure75" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/407210" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">75</figureCitation>
) is a long, simple, monotonous buzz with easily audible fibrillation, lasting from one minute to many minutes without interruption, on average 186 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Â±">+/-</normalizedToken>
187 s (
<bibRefCitation author="Sueur, Jerome" journalOrPublisher="Revue Francaise d'Entomologie (Nouvelle Serie)" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="105 - 111" refId="B5743732" refString="Sueur, Jerome, Puissant, Stephane, Pillet, J - M M, 2003. An eastern Mediterranean cicada in the west: first record of Tibicina steveni (Krynicki, 1837) in Switzerland and France [Hemiptera, Cicadidae, Tibicininae]. Revue Francaise d'Entomologie (Nouvelle Serie) 25 (3): 105 - 111" title="An eastern Mediterranean cicada in the west: first record of Tibicina steveni (Krynicki, 1837) in Switzerland and France [Hemiptera, Cicadidae, Tibicininae]" volume="25" year="2003">Sueur et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hertach, Thomas" journalOrPublisher="PLOS One" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" refId="B5792679" refString="Hertach, Thomas, 2020. Look closely and listen carefully: unexpected cicada diversity in northern Sardinia, with the description of a new species (Cicadidae: Tibicina). In: Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society." title="Look closely and listen carefully: unexpected cicada diversity in northern Sardinia, with the description of a new species (Cicadidae: Tibicina)" volumeTitle="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society." year="2020">Hertach 2020</bibRefCitation>
). It consists of a long, sustained sequence of groups of pulses (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 75" captionStartId="F5781694" captionText="Figure 75. Calling song of Tibicina steveni. (A) spectrogram and oscillogram of the selected part of the calling song; (B) oscillogram of the enlarged part corresponding to the inverted window in (A); (C) detailed oscillogram showing subgroups of pulses corresponding to the inverted window in (B); (D) detailed oscillogram showing pulses corresponding to the inverted window in (C)." figureDoi=".figure75" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/407210" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">75</figureCitation>
C) with a slow increase in amplitude at the beginning. The groups of pulses are generated at a rate of 58.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Â±">+/-</normalizedToken>
3.9 per second, the pulse-group duration is 12.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Â±">+/-</normalizedToken>
1.3 ms and the pulse-group period is 16.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Â±">+/-</normalizedToken>
1.0 ms. The pulse-groups consists of 9-10 pulses (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 75" captionStartId="F5781694" captionText="Figure 75. Calling song of Tibicina steveni. (A) spectrogram and oscillogram of the selected part of the calling song; (B) oscillogram of the enlarged part corresponding to the inverted window in (A); (C) detailed oscillogram showing subgroups of pulses corresponding to the inverted window in (B); (D) detailed oscillogram showing pulses corresponding to the inverted window in (C)." figureDoi=".figure75" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/407210" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424">75</figureCitation>
D) (
<bibRefCitation author="Sueur, Jerome" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="481 - 492" refId="B5743682" refString="Sueur, Jerome, Aubin, Thierry, 2003. Specificity of cicada calling songs in the genus Tibicina (Hemiptera: Cicadidae). Systematic Entomology 28 (4): 481 - 492" title="Specificity of cicada calling songs in the genus Tibicina (Hemiptera: Cicadidae)" volume="28" year="2003">Sueur and Aubin 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sueur, Jerome" journalOrPublisher="Revue Francaise d'Entomologie (Nouvelle Serie)" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="105 - 111" refId="B5743732" refString="Sueur, Jerome, Puissant, Stephane, Pillet, J - M M, 2003. An eastern Mediterranean cicada in the west: first record of Tibicina steveni (Krynicki, 1837) in Switzerland and France [Hemiptera, Cicadidae, Tibicininae]. Revue Francaise d'Entomologie (Nouvelle Serie) 25 (3): 105 - 111" title="An eastern Mediterranean cicada in the west: first record of Tibicina steveni (Krynicki, 1837) in Switzerland and France [Hemiptera, Cicadidae, Tibicininae]" volume="25" year="2003">Sueur et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The frequency range of the calling song is between 5.5 and 9.5 kHz with three frequency peaks: a frequency band with the highest energy at 7.2 kHz with two lateral frequency bands at about 6.4 kHz and 8.2 kHz, the lateral bands being generated by pulse amplitude modulations (
<bibRefCitation author="Sueur, Jerome" journalOrPublisher="Revue Francaise d'Entomologie (Nouvelle Serie)" pageId="0" pageNumber="54424" pagination="105 - 111" refId="B5743732" refString="Sueur, Jerome, Puissant, Stephane, Pillet, J - M M, 2003. An eastern Mediterranean cicada in the west: first record of Tibicina steveni (Krynicki, 1837) in Switzerland and France [Hemiptera, Cicadidae, Tibicininae]. Revue Francaise d'Entomologie (Nouvelle Serie) 25 (3): 105 - 111" title="An eastern Mediterranean cicada in the west: first record of Tibicina steveni (Krynicki, 1837) in Switzerland and France [Hemiptera, Cicadidae, Tibicininae]" volume="25" year="2003">Sueur et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
